==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|absinthium|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἀψίνθιον|tr=apsinthion|lang=grc}}, {{term|sc=polytonic| ἀσπίνθιον|tr=apsinthion|lang=grc}}.  The Ancient Greek word is of uncertain origin, albeit recognized as foreign (E.R. Wharton):  underlain by a pre-Greek  [[w:Pelasgians#Pelasgian_as_pre-Indo-European|Pelasgian]] word, marked by the non-Indoeuropean consonant complex νθ.
May be from {{etyl|fa}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|اسپند|tr=ispand||wild rue|lang=fa}}. See also [[w:Absinthe#Etymology|Absinthe on Wikipedia]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/æb.ˈsɪn.θi.əm/}}

